subject: Re: [junit] JUnit (junit3.8.1) - Can I Test C# lenguage?
msgSnippet: ... JUnit is only for applications that can have a Java client. A C# web service could have a Java client. It might not be a good idea, but it s certainly
messageBody:
Bradley, Todd wrote:
> 1) JUnit generally isn't thought of as a performance test tool, though
> there are extensions to it to help in that area.
>
> 2) JUnit is only for Java. You should look into NUnit, located here:
> http://www.nunit.org/.

JUnit is only for applications that can have a Java client. A C# web
service could have a Java client. It might not be a good idea, but it's
certainly possible, and it might be a good idea for /someone/.
--
J. B. (Joe) Rainsberger
Diaspar Software Services
http://www.diasparsoftware.com
Author, JUnit Recipes: Practical Methods for Programmer Testing
